<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870304-0059 </DOCNO><HL> Transamerica Unit Slates Sale</HL><DD> 03/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TATENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> SAN FRANCISCO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Transamerica Corp. said its Transamerica Occidental Life Insurance Co. unit agreed to sell its Australian affiliate to Pratt andamp; Co. Financial Services, Melbourne, for $70 million.    Transamerica, an insurance and financial-services concern, said the sale of the affiliate, Occidental Life Insurance Co. of Australia, will result in an after-tax gain of about $10 million for its insurance unit. Transamerica said proceeds of the sale will help finance Transamerica Occidental's previously announced plans to expand its North American operations. </TEXT></DOC>